data.enText: to give sth officially to sb/sth for a particular purpose
They intend to allocate more places to mature students this year.
data.chText: 今年他们打算给成人学生提供更多的名额。

data.enText: A large sum has been allocated for buying new books for the library.
data.chText: 已划拨了一大笔款子给图书馆购买新书。

data.enText: More resources are being allocated to the project.
data.chText: 正在调拨更多的资源给这个项目。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: The project is being allocated more resources.
data.chText: 这个项目正获得更多的资源。

ex.enText: We must allocate the same amount of prize money to each person concerned.
ex.chText: 我们必须把奖金平分给有关人员。

ex.enText: The government allocated the poor some money.
ex.chText: 政府向穷人分发了一些钱。

ex.enText: Two million dollars was allocated for disaster relief.
ex.chText: 已经拨出两百万美元用于救灾。

synonyms.bx: 尤指在正式决定之后将某物用于特定的目的、给予某人等，可后接双宾语。

ex.enText: You should allot 3 hours a day for revision.
ex.chText: 你应该每天抽出3个小时复习。

ex.enText: Everyone who works for the corporation has been allotted 50 shares.
ex.chText: 该公司的每位员工分到50股股票。

synonyms.bx: 尤指将特定的时间、金钱、空间等分给某人或某事，可后接双宾语。

ex.enText: Food and water have been distributed among the refugees.
ex.chText: 已经向难民分发了食物和水。

ex.enText: Do you know the man distributing leaflets to passers-by?
ex.chText: 你认识那名向路人派发传单的男子吗？

tr: distribute according to a plan or set apart for a special purpose
example: I am allocating a loaf of bread to everyone on a daily basis
I'm allocating the rations for the camping trip

example.ex: Tickets are limited and will be allocated to those who apply first...
example.tran: 票数有限，先申请者先得。

example.ex: The 1985 federal budget allocated $7.3 billion for development programmes...
example.tran: 1985年的联邦预算将73亿美元拨给了开发项目。

example.ex: Our plan is to allocate one member of staff to handle appointments.
example.tran: 我们的计划是分派一位职员处理预约事宜。

gramarinfo.label: Also V n n, V n

value.def: If one item or share of something is allocated to a particular person or for a particular purpose, it is given to that person or used for that purpose.
